# ğŸ” 1ï¸âƒ£ ss Command (Modern Replacement for netstat)

`ss` displays socket statistics and active network connections.

## Show all listening ports
```bash
ss -tuln
````

## Show TCP connections

```bash
ss -t
```

## Show UDP connections

```bash
ss -u
```

